  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><p>1. Project Oversight</p><p>Supervise and coordinate daily on-site activities to ensure projects are completed on time and within budget.</p><p>Monitor progress and report to project managers or senior engineers.</p><p>2. Team Management</p><p>Manage construction workers, subcontractors, and other personnel on site.</p><p>Assign tasks and ensure that everyone follows safety regulations and work procedures.</p><p>3. Safety and Compliance</p><p>Enforce safety standards and conduct regular inspections to minimize hazards.</p><p>Ensure compliance with local building codes, environmental regulations, and company policies.</p><p>4. Quality Control</p><p>Inspect completed work to ensure it meets specifications and standards.</p><p>Address any quality issues promptly and coordinate corrective actions.</p><p>5. Material and Equipment Management</p><p>Monitor the use of materials and equipment on site.</p><p>Ensure timely delivery and proper storage of materials and tools.</p><p>6. Problem Solving</p><p>Resolve on-site issues, such as delays, resource shortages, or design conflicts.</p><p>Communicate and collaborate with engineers, architects, and clients as needed.</p><p>7. Documentation and Reporting</p><p>Maintain accurate records of work progress, delays, incidents, and site conditions.</p><p>Prepare daily or weekly reports for upper management.</p><p>Available to work six days a week, with flexibility to return on Sundays in case of emergencies</p>",
